law.text:
To encourage the preservation of natural resources or the provision of affordable housing and to facilitate orderly development and growth, a local jurisdiction that exercises authority granted by this division may enact, and is encouraged to enact, local laws providing for or requiring:
the planning, staging, or provision of adequate public facilities and affordable housing;
off-site improvements or the dedication of land for public facilities essential for a development;
moderately priced dwelling unit programs;
mixed use developments;
cluster developments;
planned unit developments;
alternative subdivision requirements that:
meet minimum performance standards set by the local jurisdiction; and
reduce infrastructure costs;
floating zones;
incentive zoning; and
performance zoning.
